name: Miss Pipe Cleaner
description:
As part of Rogue Galleries 2013, Cherry Head transformed a pop-up studio into her very own Hoop Coop to make a collection of costumes for performance, on the condition that the costumes were made from hoops.

Hoop Trooper Pipe Cleaner is, well, made entirely from pipe cleaners!

name: Mz Twirly TuTu
description:
As part of Rogue Galleries 2013, Cherry Head transformed a pop-up studio into her very own Hoop Coop to make a collection of costumes for performance, on the condition that all of the costumes were made from hoops.


Mz TuTu is the product of hooped hose pipe within layers of mesh fabric; she of course has accessories, including a fascinator and muffler!

name: Glitter Glam Geisha Hoop Trooper
description:
As part of Rogue Galleries 2013, Cherry Head transformed a pop-up studio into her very own Hoop Coop to make a collection of costumes for performance, on the condition that the costumes were made from hoops.

This Hoop Troop-er is made from many sheets of glitter foam, hand-sewn together to make the fascinator, waistband and waistcoat, while the tutu skirt is made from garden wire of various thicknesses.

name: The Community Wedding
description:
As part of Rogue Galleries 2013, Cherry Head transformed a pop-up studio into her very own Hoop Coop to make a collection of costumes for performance, on the condition that the costumes were made from hoops.

Everyone who visited the Hoop Coop was asked to decorate a paper plate (which is a hoop in itself, and so the participant had free rein on their design!)

Cherry Head then took all 200 decorated plates and started to layer and mould them over a hosepipe circular frame, then also a bodice, and finally a veil and bouquet of flowers. Where better to photograph the Community Wedding dress than outside a cathedral?!

name: Trooper Woolen Wiggle
description:
As part of Rogue Galleries 2013, Cherry Head transformed a pop-up studio into her very own Hoop Coop to make a collection of costumes for performance, on the condition that the costumes were made from hoops.


Wiggle Ziggle is made from hoops of hosepipe suspended with numerous balls of wool, from head to toe. Her ziggling wiggling ability allows her to blend into any situation!
